    <stitle>No Idle APU/HVAC System - MAINTENANCE - Checking Level and Adding Engine Oil</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Checking Level and Adding Engine Oil</title>
        <figure id="f1603716" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603716.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 16. Checking/Adding Engine Oil</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check engine oil level before starting or more than 5 minutes after stopping engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove engine oil dipstick, wipe it clean and re-install it.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove dipstick and check oil level - see illustration.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If oil level is low, remove the oil filler plug and add new oil to the appropriate level.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After adding oil, wait more than 5 minutes to verify oil level. It takes some time for oil
                to fall into the oil pan.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Be sure to check engine oil with engine on a horizontal surface. Placing the engine on gradients
                    could result in inaccurate engine oil level readings.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
